label.value: Viral Half Maximal Inhibitory Concentration Subject Result Measurement

value.value: A measurement of titer of a viral organism or biological/biochemical reaction that has been exposed to a concentration of a specific drug expected to produce 50% inhibition of the standard growth of the viral organism, or of a reaction.

label.value: Viral Half Maximal Inhibitory Concentration Reference Control Result Measurement

value.value: A reference control sample response based on a concentration of a specific drug expected to produce 50% inhibition of the standard growth of a viral organism, or of a biological/biochemical reaction.

label.value: Viral Half Maximal Inhibitory Concentration Fold Change from Reference Measurement

value.value: A fold change based on a concentration of a specific drug expected to produce 50% inhibition of the standard growth of a viral organism, or of a biological/biochemical reaction. It is a ratio calculated by the IC50 Treatment Result divided by the IC50 Reference Control Result.

label.value: Viral Half Maximal Inhibitory Concentration Fold Change from Baseline Measurement

value.value: A fold change based on a concentration of a specific drug expected to produce 50% inhibition of the standard growth of a viral organism, or of a biological/biochemical reaction. It is a ratio calculated by the current IC50 Treatment Result divided by the IC50 Treatment Result from the baseline visit.

label.value: Viral 95 Percent Maximal Inhibitory Concentration Subject Result Measurement

label.value: Viral 95 Percent Maximal Inhibitory Concentration Fold Change from Reference Measurement

label.value: Viral 95 Percent Maximal Inhibitory Concentration Fold Change from Baseline Measurement

value.value: A fold change based on a concentration of a specific drug expected to produce 95% inhibition of the standard growth of a viral organism, or of a biological/biochemical reaction. It is a ratio calculated by the current IC95 Treatment Result divided by the IC95 Treatment Result from the baseline visit.

This gene is involved in second messenger synthesis.

Human PLCD3 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17q21.31 and is approximately 24 kb in length. This allele, which encodes 1-phosphatidylinositol 4,5-bisphosphate phosphodiesterase delta-3 protein, plays a role in the synthesis of second messenger signaling molecules. Variation in the gene is associated with dichotomous hypertension.

1-phosphatidylinositol 4,5-bisphosphate phosphodiesterase delta-3 (789 aa, ~89 kDa) is encoded by the human PLCD3 gene. This protein is involved in the generation of second messenger molecules from phosphoinositides.
